HEADWORD: Savoy
<hw>Sa*voy"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>chou de
Savoie</ets> cabbage of Savoy.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A variety
of the common cabbage (<spn>Brassica oleracea major</spn>), having
curled leaves, -- much cultivated for winter use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

